item.description:
If there is a way to be indifferent to all things, then that method requires that one be indifferent to &ldquo;indifference&rdquo; itself. In other words, indifference that &ldquo;allows indifference,&rdquo; this is called the &ldquo;Law of Great Indifference&rdquo; or &ldquo;Great Forbearance.&rdquo;
In contrast, the method of not allowing oneself to be shaken under any circumstances is called the &ldquo;method of small indifference&rdquo; or &ldquo;small patience.&rdquo;
Taking an object as an example, in the first stage you can only be moved by that object.
